com.ibm.team.scm.common.dto

Interface ILockSearchCriteria

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.ibm.team.scm.common.internal.INamedSearchCritieria, ISearchCriteria

    public interface ILockSearchCriteria
extends com.ibm.team.scm.common.internal.INamedSearchCritieria, ISearchCriteria
    This interface defines the criteria that locks can match. Every criteria can either be set or unset (set to null). When multiple criteria are set the result is the conjunction of all the criteria.
    Since:
    0.7

      • getContributor

      • setContributor

        Parameters:
        contributor - - the lock owner

      • getStreams

        java.util.Collection<IWorkspaceHandle> getStreams()
        The collection of streams in which to search for locks. If the collection is empty then search for locks in any stream. Specifying more than IScmQueryService.MAX_PAGE_SIZE streams will result in an IllegalArgumentException when searching.
        Returns:
        A collection to which stream handles should be added to scope the search.

      • getComponents

        java.util.Collection<IComponentHandle> getComponents()
        The collection of components in which to search for locks. If the collection is empty then search for locks in any component. If getStreams() is not empty, then the search will be scoped to components in those specified stream. Specifying more than IScmQueryService.MAX_PAGE_SIZE components will result in an IllegalArgumentException when searching.
        Returns:
        A collection to which component handles should be added to scope the search

      • getVersionables

        java.util.Collection<IVersionableHandle> getVersionables()
        The collection of versionables to search for locks on. If the collection is empty, then search for lock on any versionable. If getStreams() or getComponents() are not empty, then the search will be restricted to the specified versionables in those streams/components. Specifying more than IScmQueryService.MAX_PAGE_SIZE versionables will result in an IllegalArgumentException when searching.
        Returns:
        A collection to which versionable handles should be added to scope the search

        Set a string prefix for searching the versionable locks. Only one of setExactName(String) setPartialName(String) and setPartialNameIgnoreCase(String) will have effect. The last one called will determine the matching strategy
